<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Southwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake of 5.0 on the
Richter Scale rocked Mianzhu city of southwest China province of
Sichuan on 20:54 (Beijing time) today, the China Seismological
Bureau announced here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was located at 31.6 degrees north
latitude and 104.1 degrees east longitude, according to the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt in Chengdu, capital of the province, the
bureau said.
</P>
<P>
So far, there is no report about housing damages or casualties.
</P>
</TEXT>
