<HEADLINE> Thailand to Promote International Conferences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday
approved a marketing strategy for the promotion of international
conferences in Thailand, according to a Government House press
release.
</P>
<P>
The strategy, proposed by the Tourism Authority of Thailand
(TAT), urges government agencies and state enterprises to organize
international conferences and exhibitions at home other than
abroad.
</P>
<P>
TAT hopes the agencies concerned can hold international
conferences in provincial areas.
</P>
<P>
It also encourages the private sector to hold conferences and
exhibitions in Thailand or offer the prize of domestic tour
packages, in which the expenditure can be deducted from the annual
tax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
