<HEADLINE> Italy Ready to Send Contingent to East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 14 (xinhua) -- The Italian contingent that may
be involved in the peace-keeping mission in East Timor is "ready
now" for departure, Italian Defense Minister Carlo Scognamiglio
said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Before a hearing of the House Defense Commission, Scognamiglio
stressed that as soon as the U.N. Security Council gives its
go-ahead, "Italian soldiers will be operative in Timor within 15
days' time."
</P>
<P>
"As far as the characteristics of the contingent are
concerned," he added, "we're waiting for the U.N. resolution this
afternoon -- evening for us. Only then will we be able to announce
the extent of our participation."
</P>
<P>
"We have 200-250 men available," he said, "which means two
operative companies plus the logistical support and an amphibious
ship that can ensure the transport of logistics and part of the
troops." 
</P>
