<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Cuba Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and Cuba have
pledged to promote economic, scientific and technical cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Vice Minister of Economic Development and Cooperation
Mulatu Teshome and his Cuban counterpart Noemi de Mendoza signed
an agreement to the effect here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Both Mulatu and Mendoza expressed that the agreement, which is
to be implemented soon, would further strengthen the existing
bilateral relations between Ethiopia and Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Cuba established diplomatic relations in 1976.
Cuba provided support to Ethiopia in education, health and defense
in late 1970' s and 1980's.
</P>
<P>
Some 4,000 Ethiopians received education in Cuba, according to
an official statistics. 
</P>
