<HEADLINE> U.N. Food Aid to Reach Angola's Province in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,000 tons of food aid
are expected to reach Angola's northern province of Malanje in
September, the United Nations Humanitarian Assistance Coordination
Unit said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In Malanje, one of the provinces which has been experiencing
the most fierce civil war, the displaced people are suffering
hunger.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. humanitarian unit said in a document that the number
of canteens for the displaced and the communitarian infantile
program in Malanje has increased from 74 to 93, benefiting about
6,600 people.
</P>
<P>
The assistance activities continue to be realized under
increasing risk and pressure in limited areas of the southern
African country which has suffered over 25 years of civil
conflicts, it added.
</P>
<P>
However, the humanitarian situation in Angola continues to
worry the local authorities, with the lack of access to the
population in need, the scarcity of fuel and security as the
principal constraints.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. agency also revealed that the enormous afflux of
displaced people maintains in most parts of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
