<HEADLINE> Uganda Sets Precondition for Withdrawal from Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We would pull out of Congo if all the parties who signed the
agreement honor it," the president told reporters at the State
House.
</P>
<P>
But he also said that "the prospects of the DRC peace process
are good."
</P>
<P>
However, the president noted that if Uganda could not beat the
deadline, it was the Goma faction to blame as the faction has
delayed in signing the peace accord reached in Zambian capital
Lusaka on July 10 by the six countries directly involved in the
DRC conflict.
</P>
<P>
When asked what Uganda, as a country, benefited from its
military presence in the vast central African country, Museveni
said that the presence of the Uganda People's Defense Forces
there has contributed greatly to the improved security within the
east African country by weakening, in particular, the activities
of the Allied Democratic Forces(ADF), a rebel group in western
Uganda.
