he further explained. Apart from security concerns, Uganda is
concerned about economy, development and solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Uganda began to deploy its forces in the eastern part of the
DRC soon after a rebellion erupted in the latter in early August
last year.
</P>
<P>
Kampala said that its military presence in the third largest
African country is to protect the safety of its western border by
pushing and killing the ADF rebels.
</P>
<P>
Under the Lusaka agreement signed by all the parties concerned,
all foreign forces should pull out of the troubled DRC within 180
days after the official endorsement of the peace accord.
</P>
<P>
Both the Goma and Kisangani factions of the main rebel group,
the Congolese Rally for Democracy, did not ink the pact because of
their internal wrangling until the end of last month. 
</P>
