<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Assembly Opens New Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly
(GA) Tuesday afternoon opened its 54th session at the United
Nations headquarters in New York, the first GA which is about to
straddle two millennia.
</P>
<P>
Didier Opertti, who was president of the just-concluded 53rd
session and head of the delegation of Uruguay, declared the
opening of the 54th GA session.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan and Jin Yongjian,
under-secretary-general, were present at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Theo-Ben Gurirab, Namibian foreign minister, was elected
president of the 54th GA session.
</P>
<P>
In his acceptance speech, the new president said, "There are
present and future challenges that face us as we enter the coming
age." They are globalization, sustainable development and the
protection of environment, regional war, the ever-deteriorating
refugee crisis, gender equality, the HIV/AIDS pandemic, and the
future of children in a globalized community.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first ever General Assembly to straddle two
millennia," he said. "The aspiration, hopes and expectations of
the world's peoples are high as they anticipate the future."
</P>
<P>
"They yearn for a world that is peaceful, humane and prosperous
for all," he said. "Without the U.N., such an inclusive world led
by inspiring leaders cannot come about."
</P>
<P>
The new president also called on all member states to "pay
their contributions on time and without preconditions."
</P>
<P>
"Without adequate resources, the U.N. cannot perform
effectively," he said.
</P>
<P>
At present, the largest debtor is the United States, who owed
the United Nations 1.6 billion U.S. dollars in arrears. Under the
U.N. Charter it will automatically lose its vote at the General
Assembly next year if it fails to pay at least 350 million U.S.
dollars by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly is the main deliberative organ. It is
composed of representatives of all member states, each of which
has one vote.
</P>
<P>
The GA regular session usually begins each year in September.
At the start of each regular session, the Assembly elects a new
president, 21 vice-presidents and the chairpersons of its six main
committees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
