<HEADLINE> Balkanization Should Be Stopped in Africa: Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni said here Tuesday that Balkanization should be stopped in
the African continent.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at a press conference in the evening when
asked about the outcome of his talks with Libyan leader Muammar
Gaddafi at the 4th extraordinary summit of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) in Libyan coastal city of Sirte last week.
</P>
<P>
"I advocate that Africa should go ahead with the economic
integration as expressed in Abuja agreement in 1991," Museveni
said. "I totally agree with Gaddafi in that Balkanization should
be stopped."
</P>
<P>
"But I am not interested in idea of United States of Africa,"
he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"You can do business with anyone disregarding his ideology,
his culture and so on. But political union is a much closer
relationship. Africa has 54 countries, most of them are small and
weak, that's why I oppose Balkanization," he added. 
</P>
