<HEADLINE> International Arms Fair Starts in London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- One of the world's most famous
arms fair, Defense System and Equipment International(DSEI),
opened on Tuesday here in London.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,000 arms manufacturers from Britain, the United
States, Western Europe and Russia laid out their wares at the
fair, which was opened by British Defense Secretary George
Robertson.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech to the conference and exhibition held in
Surry, south London, Robertson denied helping to arm the
aggressors of East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Under heavy pressure from both domestic and international
sides, British government had been forced to rethink its position
on arms sale to Indonesia, while Jakarta had to turn down an offer
to visit this international arms fair held currently in Britain.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Britain is one of the world's leading arms
exporters with 9,000 firms involved in defense equipment
manufacturing that provides 355,000 jobs.
</P>
<P>
Amnesty International has complained that Britain's willingness
to do business with countries that had a poor human rights record
was undermining Britain's ethical foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Also on Tuesday, several groups of people held demonstrations
outside the compound where the DSEI exhibition and conference
were held, in which thousands of businessmen were negotiating
their arms sales.
</P>
<P>
They held placards and shouted slogans to protest against arms
proliferation, especially against British arms sales to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition was scheduled to end on Friday. A series of
conferences on "the challenge of warfare", technology, "theater
ballistic missile defense" and other issues are also planned to be
held during the period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
