<HEADLINE> Africa Urged to Rely on Itself in Fighting AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has urged the African countries to ensure that
adequate resources are allocated to the prevention of AIDS in
their budgets.
</P>
<P>
The African governments should not rely on support from donor
countries as far as the fight against AIDS in concerned, OAU
representative Mahamat Habib Doutoum said in Lusaka Tuesday at the
on-going 11th International Conference on AIDS and STDS (sexually
transmitted diseases) in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Doutoum said that donor countries would only be compelled to
assist if the African governments themselves start committing
enough resources to AIDS prevention in their budgets.
</P>
<P>
It is time that African governments start taking AIDS as a real
 challenge and develop strategies aimed at combating the disease,
the OAU official noted.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for governments to improve working
conditions for their health workers as the fight against AIDS goes
on.
</P>
<P>
Focus should be on women as AIDS awareness campaigns are
carried out because they are more vulnerable to the disease, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
