<HEADLINE> Panama Issues 150 Million Dollars Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian government
authorized the issuing of 150 million dollars Treasury Bonds as a
measure to fill the empty state coffers, said the Official Gazette
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Treasury Bonds, which were originally approved by the
previous government of Ernesto Perez Balllardes, will be brought up
by the Social Security Agency (CSS) by way of the National Bank of
Panama (BNP) for a 12 year-term.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate to be paid by the BNP is 8.5 percent, more
than double the normal payment of below 5 percent, and also higher
than that paid by the private banking sector in both Panama and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
According to financial analysts, the Treasury Bonds will be
snapped up, as much for their high interest rates, as for their
exemption from tax. 
</P>
