<HEADLINE> S. Africa Rejects Angola's Appeal for Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
Foreign Minister Aziz Pahad Tuesday rejected with contempt an
appeal by his Angolan counterpart for sanctions against South
Africa, state television reported.
</P>
<P>
Angolan deputy foreign minister, George Chicoty, said last
Friday that South Africa and several other countries should be
penalized for not doing enough to stop violations of U.N. embargo
against the rebels of the National Union for Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
In response, Pahad said Chicoty's statement was "very
surprising" and needed to be dealt with contempt, noting that
South Africa was abiding by all U.N. resolutions on the UNITA.
</P>
