<HEADLINE> John Lennon Guitar Sold for 155,000 Pounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The guitar that John Lennon
was playing on the day he met Paul McCartney was sold for 155,000
pounds (249,200 U.S. dollars) on Tuesday night, auctioneers
Sotheby's said.
</P>
<P>
Lennon, the creator of Beatles, bought the acoustic Gallotone
Champion instrument for 10 pounds (16 dollars) about a month
before meeting McCartney at a Liverpool church fete on July 6,
1957.
</P>
<P>
The guitar was the earliest Beatles-related guitar to come on
to auction market. It was bought by a New York investment fund
manager, who bid by telephone and declined to be named.
</P>
<P>
The final figure exceeded the expectations of Sotheby's, which
had estimated the guitar would fetch up to 100,000 pounds.
</P>
<P>
On the neck of the guitar is a plaque which recalls what Lennon
was once told by his Aunt Mimi: "Remember, you'll never earn your
living by it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
