<HEADLINE> Montpelier Edge Crvena Zvezda in UEFA Pro Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Crvena Zvezda of Yugoslavia
lost to Montpelier of France 0-1 in a first-round, first-leg match
of the UEFA Pro Cup Tournament at Sofia's Georgi Asparouhov
Stadium on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The only goal came from Patrice Loko six minutes into the first
half. Dejan Ilic of Crvena Zvezda was sent off in the 57th minute.
</P>
<P>
The fixture took place in Sofia because UEFA banned Serbian
teams from hosting European club tournament matches in Yugoslavia
for the poor transportation services caused by damaged
infrastructure in the country as a result of the U.S.-led NATO
bombing. Crvena Zvezda chose the alternative venue.
</P>
<P>
The match was watched by a crowd of 11,000 including some 2,000
Yugoslavian fans, and was policed by some 300 uniformed officers.
The Serbian and the French fans were separated in different
sectors of the stands.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade Mayor Vojislav Mihajlovic also attended the game but
declined to comment after the final whistle. 
</P>
