<HEADLINE> Sluggish Start for Manchester United in Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Manchester
United had a sluggish start on the opening night of Champions
League first group phase when they were held to a 0-0 draw by
Croatia Zagreb on Tuesday
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Dynamo Kiev had a shock home defeat and Barcelona
gained a hard-fought victory with a late goal.
</P>
<P>
Lazio, ambitious to add the European Cup to the Cup Winners'
Cup trophy they won last season, were held to a 1-1 draw by Bayer
Leverkusen in Germany, while Arsenal's Nigerian striker Nwankwo
Kanu wasted a chance to give his side an opening victory when his
late penalty was saved by Fiorentina's Italian international
keeper Francesco Toldo.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, fielding some unfamiliar names in a
makeshift side after injury and ineligibility ravaged Alex
Ferguson's squad, were held to a 0-0 draw at Old Trafford by
Croatia Zagreb in group D.
</P>
<P>
In the same group Olympique Marseille, back in the competition
for the first time since winning it in 1993, cruised to a 2-0 win
over Sturm Graz of Austria with goals from Robert Pires and
Fabrizio Ravanelli.
</P>
<P>
There was a major upset in Kiev where Maribor Teatanic of
Slovenia upset last year's semi-finalists Dynamo 1-0, with a goal
from Ante Simundza 16 minutes from the end of their Group A match.
</P>
<P>
Lazio's draw in Leverkusen came in the same section. Both
goals came in the opening spell with Oliver Neuville scoring for
the Germans after 14 minutes and Sinisa Mihajlovic equalising with
a blistering free kick four minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona left it late to win their Group B match in Stockholm
with headers from Abelardo Fernandez at the 86th minute and Dani
Garcia, deep into injury time, giving the Catalans victory after
Nebosja Novakovic's goal at the 73rd minute put AIK ahead.
</P>
<P>
With Fiorentina and Arsenal drawing in Florence, Barcelona go
to the top of what looks to be the toughest group in the
competition.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian champions Rosenborg Trondheim had no worries beating
Boavista 3-0 in Portugal with Jan Derek Sorensen (8), Orjan Berg (
43) and Roar Strand (73) securing an easy Group C victory.
</P>
<P>
Feyenoord drew 1-1 with Borussia Dortmund in the same group in
Rotterdam. Kees van Wonderen put the Dutch champions ahead after
66 minutes with Fredi Bobic equalising for the Germans five
minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Eight matches in Groups E to H will be played Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
