<HEADLINE> Guatemalan President to Visit Cuba in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Guatemalan President
Alvaro Arzu will make an official visit to Cuba in October,
according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first official visit by a Guatemalan president
to Cuba since the restoration of diplomatic relations between the
two countries in January 1998, after 36 years of suspension.
</P>
<P>
Arzu announced Tuesday that he will meet with his Cuban
counterpart Fidel Castro during his stay in the Caribbean island
country.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan exporters of vegetables and textiles are
enthusiastic about the visit as they hope to tap new market for
their products, said President Arzu.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan Foreign Minister Eduardo Stein said the two
governments want to strengthen bilateral relations in all fields.
During the forthcoming visit, trade and economic issues will be
given first priority. 
