<HEADLINE> Thirteen Colombian Farmers Killed by Rival Paramilitary Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 farmers
were shot dead by rival paramilitary groups Monday evening in the
provinces of Cordoba and Cauca, Colombia, authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A group of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC)
took five farm workers from their dwellings in Cordoba and shot
them, accusing them of being collaborators of the Auto-defence
Units of Colombia (AUC), a rival paramilitary group, said Franklin
de la Vega, secretary of the province.
</P>
<P>
In a revenging shooting spree, members of AUC killed eight
farmers in the south-east province of Cauca, in the same day with
the same excuse, local police said. 
</P>
