<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africans Takes Athletics Medals at All Africa Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Athletics gave South
Africa a lift in the medals tally as they pulled off a seven-medal
haul of four golds, two silvers and a bronze on the opening day of
the track and field action in the All Africa Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Burger Lambrechts led a 1-2-3 South African sweep in the shot
put with a 19.50 meters performance. Janus Robberts claimed the
silver with 19.16m, with Karel Potgieter touching down at 18.9m
for the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Other gold medals were captured by hammer thrower Chris Haremse,
javelin specialist Liezel Roux and Rika Erasmus, an upset winner
in the women's pole vault.
</P>
<P>
Hezekiel Sepeng, silver medalist at last month's world
championships in Seville and a favorite for the 800m gold here
against a powerful field of Kenyans, raced in pain to qualify for
the semi-finals on Wednesday after arriving earlier in the day
from Europe.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's Assefa Mezgebu, fourth at the world championships,
sprinted to gold on a winning time of 28 minutes 12.15 seconds in
men's 10,000m.
</P>
<P>
Egypt narrowly edged out South Africa in the final medal count
at the Games men's gymnastic competition on Tuesday, by a score
total of 20 to 19.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's under-23 soccer team reached the semi-finals when they
thrashed Mauritius in their last group match Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Zambians finished second to Cameroon, held to a 1-1 tie by
Cote d'Ivoire on Tuesday, in Group Two and they will meet Group
One leaders South Africa in the semi-finals later in the week.
Cameroon will meet Group One runners-up Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Samir scored a late equalizer for Egypt to snatch a 2-2
draw against Kenya in one of the most exciting All Africa Games
men's field hockey matches Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyans dominated play for a large part of the game and
caught the ill-disciplined Egyptians off-guard with their
impressive play.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's women's team, however, lost 3-2 to Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The South African men's tennis team moved inexorably towards
the gold medal at Ellis Park on Tuesday with a 3-0 win over
Mauritius.
</P>
<P>
The top seeds now face Namibia in Thursday's semi-finals and
that is one tie the South Africans are not going to lose for a win
there will guarantee them at least the silver. Second seeds Cote
d'Ivoire and number three Mauritius will meet in the other semi-
final fixture.
</P>
<P>
The South African women's team will play their semi-finals tie
Wednesday against Zimbabwe while in the other half, second seeds
Madagascar take on Algeria.
</P>
<P>
South Africa emerged as unbeaten champions of the All Africa
Games netball in Soweto near Johannesburg and claimed the gold
medal after beating Malawi 74-35 in the final match of the
tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
