<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Strengthen Ties with Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Vietnamese
Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam said here Tuesday that his
government has a desire to strengthen ties with Argentina.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting with his Argentine counterpart Guido di Tella,
Nguyen Manh Cam told a press conference that it is necessary to
boost cooperation between the two countries in various fields, as
much in politics as in economy, trade and culture.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries already have agreements
protecting and promoting investments as well as documents
enhancing economic, commercial, and scientific and technological
cooperation, which provide legal basis for further development of
friendship.
</P>
<P>
The financial crisis in Asia has bottomed out and many
countries are recuperating their economies, he added.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Manh Cam arrived here Monday for a two-day official
visit. 
