<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Medvedev Crashed out in Bournemouth Men's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Andrei Medvedev
suffered a major blow on Tuesday when he lost in the first round
of the Bournemouth Open men's tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The fourth seed, a finalist in this year's French Open, was
beaten by Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden 6-2, 7-6.
</P>
<P>
Medvedev led 5-2 in the second set and 5-3 in the tie-break,
only to founder against his opponent's huge forehands and his own
temperamental frailties.
</P>
<P>
He was awarded a code violation warning for hitting a ball out
of the stadium just before the end.
</P>
<P>
Another seed, defending champion Felix Mantilla, also went out.
</P>
<P>
The top 20-ranked Spaniard won the first two games and then
unaccountably lost nine on the trot to go down 6-2, 6-3 to Kenneth
Carlsen of Denmark, who is ranked at 86 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Thomas Enqvist progressed 7-5, 6-1 against Swedish
compatriot Nicklas Kulti, godfather to his child. "It's always
difficult to play your best friend. We both found it difficult to
get pumped up," said Enqvist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
