<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Deputy FM, 5 Others Killed in Plane Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Greek Deputy Foreign
Minister Yiannos Kranidiotis and five other persons were killed
late Tuesday in a plane accident over Romania.
</P>
<P>
Their plane hit heavy turbulence and went into a steep dive,
Romanian Transport Minister Traian Basescu said.
</P>
<P>
Kranidiotis, 51, and his son Nikos, 23, were on their way to a
meeting in Bucharest with a Balkan cooperation group.
</P>
<P>
Five others aboard were hospitalized, while another two were
not injured. The dead and injured included journalists.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred shortly after the plane entered Romanian
airspace near Giurgiu, about 60 kilometers southeast of Bucharest.
The plane was preparing to land in Bucharest.
</P>
<P>
Basescu said the pilot lost control of the plane at 21,000 feet
and the plane plummeted thousands of feet before he could
straighten it out. The plane managed to land at Otopeni
international airport.
</P>
<P>
Romanian television reports said Kranidiotis and the others
possibly suffocated or suffered heart attacks after their aircraft
suddenly depressurized as it rapidly lost altitude. 
</P>
</TEXT>
