Jenny Shipley hold talks Tuesday. Both leaders spoke highly of the
smooth development of ties between the two countries over the past
27 years.
</P>
<P>
Both sides vowed to make concerted efforts for the
establishment of a long-term, stable, smooth and all-round
relationship of cooperation geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Shipley stressed that her country firmly supports China's entry
into the WTO at an early date and reiterated that her government
has always followed and will continue to stick to the one-China
policy.
</P>
<P>
