<HEADLINE> Canadian Airlines Cancel Flights to Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Air Canada and Canadian
Airlines International have canceled flights to Florida amid
reports of Hurricane Floyd landing at the Bahama Islands, the CTV
reported late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 passengers have been held up by the cancellations
since Monday, when they were informed of the risk of the flights.
The decision remains effective for 36 hours, the television said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2 million Americans were reported moving out of Florida
in fear of the advent of Floyd, which pounded the Bahamas Tuesday
morning with howling winds at 225 kilometers an hour.
</P>
<P>
The tropical storm is expected to reach Miami and Fort
Lauderdale, Florida, late Tuesday. 
</P>
