<HEADLINE> Moya Crashes out at First Hurdle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Carlos Moya seemed
to still nurse his injury as the Spaniard was upset by Juan
Balcells in the 500,000 U.S.dollars ATP Mallorca Open on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Moya lost the first round match 4-6, 6-3, 6-3, showing the
world's 15th-ranked player is yet to fully recovered from the back
ailment that forced him to withdraw from the recent U.S. Open.
</P>
