Earlier, Bulgarian Orlin Stanoytchev pulled off another
surprise, eliminating third-seeded Albert Costa of Spain 6-3, 6-7
(3-7), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The day saw a marathon thriller in which Argentina's Hernan
Gumy took 2 1/2 hours to down Spain's Alex Calatrava 7-6 (15-13),
4-6, 7-5, forcing delay of the match between Markus Hipfl of
Austria and Gaston Gaudio of Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Juan Alberto Viloca overcame fellow Spaniard Fernando Vicente 6-
3, 5-7, 6-4 in the first match and Slovakia's Dominik Hrbaty,
seeded fourth, brushed aside Spain's German Puentes 5-7, 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In the final match of the day, Argentine Mariano Puerta
eliminated Spain's Carlos Costa 6-4, 6-1. 
</P>
