<HEADLINE> Nicaragua to Invite Bids for Oil Exploration Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua announced Tuesday
that it would open bidding to foreign companies for petroleum
exploration and exploitation in the country next year.
</P>
<P>
The Nicaraguan Institute of Energy (INE) has confirmed the
presence of hydrocarbon reserves on the Pacific and Atlantic
coasts of the country, said Veronica Artiles, chief of an INE
survey team.
</P>
<P>
She added that there is interest from foreign companies, mainly
North American, in oil explorations in Nicaragua. 
</P>
