<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seeds Nipped in President's Cup First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one
Yevgeny Kafelnikov became the only seed to survive the first round
at the 500,000 U.S. dollars President's Cup tennis tournament in
Tashkent, Uzbekstan on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Kafelnikov overcame a dismal first set against
fellow Russian and Davis Cup teammate Andrei Cherkasov before he
made the second round with a 1-6, 6-3, 6-3 victory.
</P>
<P>
Three other seeds in action, Briton Greg Rusedski, Cedric
Pioline of France and Russian Marat Safin all became the
casualties of the first round competitions.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Rusedski bowed to Italian Laurence Tieleman 6-3, 6-
4 while sixth-seeded Russian Marat Safin trailed the unsung Finn
Ville Liukko 4-6, 7-5, 3-1 before he retired in the third set.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Frenchman Pioline, who last week reached the semi-
finals at the U.S. Open, lost to Swiss teenager Roger Federer 6-4,
6-3 in the last match of the evening session.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Slovaks Karol Kucera and Jan Kroslak, the eighth
seed of the event, had crashed out of the first round on Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
