<HEADLINE> General Motors Plans Auto-venture in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- General Motors Corp., the
world's largest automobile manufacturer, has started a joint-
venture auto company in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's
Liaoning province.
</P>
<P>
GM and the FAW-Jinbei Automobile Co., Ltd, co-financed the deal
with a total of 230 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ground has been broken for the new plant, which will cover 34,
000 square meters. The company will turn out its first car in the
fourth quarter of the year 2000 and go into operation in 2001.
</P>
<P>
The new company is projected to have an annual production
capacity of 30,000 automobiles during the first stage of operation,
and 50,000 in the second stage.
</P>
<P>
GM so far has five joint ventures in China, engaged in car
production, auto-service, and technological development. The auto
giant also has set up two research centers with Chinese
universities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
