<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province to Woo Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
will make more efforts to improve the investment environment and
attract more overseas investment needed for the coastal province's
economic take-off, said acting governor Xi Jinping.
</P>
<P>
So far Fujian has established economic and trade ties with over
100 countries and regions and overseas investors have put 27
billion U.S. dollars worth of investment into the province, said
Xi in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the acting governor said, his province will proceed
from local conditions to develop its economy and keep opening up
to increase its comprehensive strength in the next decade.
</P>
<P>
Fujian needs to continue using Deng Xiaoping Theory as its
guideline and to increase efforts to improve macro-economic
controls and agriculture, speed up reforms, and adjust the
economic structure, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xi said that the province has been working on a scientific
development program to which greater attention will be given and
more advanced technology will be used to improve the performance
of enterprises and develop pillar industries in the early years of
the next century.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has witnessed earth-shaking changes since China began
its reforms and opening up in 1978. Its improved infrastructure
has made the province particularly popular with overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The rural areas are the best place to see the great changes.
The number of poverty-stricken people in the province fell from 2.
42 million in the mid-80s to 101,900 in 1997. There has been an
improvement in the province's standard of living and production
conditions, with electricity available in almost all rural
households, phone service in 83 percent of the villages, and tap
water in 95.2 percent of the rural households.
</P>
<P>
The governor says that his province will continue its effort at
advancing agriculture and poverty-relief work in rural areas, and
at providing comfortable lives for all rural people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
