<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 6,000 Construction Projects in Beijing Pass Inspection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 6,000 construction
projects in Beijing have passed an inspection conducted by the
Beijing Municipal Construction Committee and the Beijing Municipal
Planning Committee.
</P>
<P>
The review conducted by the two committees ran from May to
August. During the period, they checked quality of 6,534
construction projects which are either completed or being built,
in three phases.
</P>
<P>
The results show that 20 percent of the approved projects are
of good quality. All are in line with their original design and
state regulations.
</P>
<P>
Among the inspected projects, 3,187 are completed and 3,347 are
underway. Forty bridges and roads were also checked.
</P>
<P>
Late last month, China passed a law on inviting and submitting
tenders to ensure construction quality and promote fair
competition.
</P>
<P>
The new law will take effect on January 1, 2000. It is meant to
improve openness and fairness in project bidding and equipment
purchasing, and also to reduce spending and improve construction
quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
