<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Knight: Revised Schedule Close to Original </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sydney 2000 Olympics
organizers have felt relieved as their original athletics programs
have been barely changed.
</P>
<P>
The International Amateur Athletics Federation (IAAF) has asked
for a day's break between the semi-finals and finals of any event
of 400 meters or longer and a two-day break for races of 3,000
meters or more.
</P>
<P>
This would require major alterations to the schedule which was
the last thing on the mind of the organizers.
</P>
<P>
Olympics Minister Michael Knight said on Wednesday that
International Olympic Committee president Juan Antonio Samaranch
informed him from Lausanne that IAAF chief Primo Nebiolo had
signed off on a slightly revised schedule for track and field
events of 400 meters or longer.
</P>
<P>
"None of those huge changes they were proposing are going to
happen," Knight said. "I've been told the revised program is much
closer to what we originally had. We are relieved and delighted."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
