<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Environmental Protection Vital to China's Sustainable Development ( 3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In tune with the public mood, legislation on environmental
protection has accelerated. Since 1979, a total of 43
environmental protection-related laws have been enacted.
</P>
<P>
The input for environmental protection has also increased
considerably over the past years. In 1998, the government's
financial allocation for environmental protection reached more
than 80 billion (9.6 billion US dollars), exceeding one percent of
the GDP for the first time. In the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (
1996-2000), budgetary spending for the same purpose will reach 450
billion yuan (54 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
China also values foreign capital for its environmental
protection drive. By the end of last year, China had successfully
drawn more than 3 billion US dollars of overseas investment and
signed cooperative contracts with 25 countries in the field of
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
It has become China's basic state policy to save natural
resources, protect the environment and realize sustainable
development. The National Ecological Environment Development Plan,
released by the State Council recently, once again demonstrates
that environmental protection has become a vital strategic step
for China in the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
