</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- The World Food Program (WFP), in conjunction with
the Rwandan National Food Committee, is planning to supply more
than 1,500 tons of food to hunger-stricken Rwandans, the Rwanda
News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Coordinator of the committee, Innocent Rwakazina, said Tuesday
that northeastern Umutara and Kibungo, and southwestern Gikongoro
are the prefectures most hit by starvation. (Rwanda-Food Relief)
</P>
