- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Stronger-than-expected US retail sales figures cooled
optimism on Europe's bourses Tuesday,driving its main stocks lower
amid rekindled fears over the outlook for interest rates.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100, which had risen about 80 points
early in the session on the back of benign domestic inflation data,
saw its gains eroded by the US data.
</P>
<P>
