<HEADLINE> Thailand's Insurance Industry Revives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's life insurance
industry is reviving with its total premium in the first seven
months of this year growing 5.59 percent to 33.82 billion baht
(890 million U.S. dollars), The Nation reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Prayuth Sangchan, director of the Thai Life Assurance
Association, was quoted as saying consumers were more interested
in buying life insurance policies now that their purchasing power
was stronger than it was last year.
</P>
<P>
Ordinary coverage had a lion's share of earnings in the sector,
accounting for 83.19 percent, which translates into 28.13 billion
baht (740 million dollars) or a 6.97-percent increase when
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Industry insurance made up 12.33 percent of the total earning
at 4.17 billion baht (109 million dollars), up by 1.58 percent,
followed by group insurance at 4.47 percent of the total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
