<HEADLINE> Tibet Tries Government Procurement System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- In an effort to increase
openness and fair dealings in government procurement, the Tibet
Autonomous Region has started testing modern methods of government
purchases in Shannan Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
A number of musical instruments costing 300,000 yuan (about 36,
275 U.S. dollars) arrived in Shannan recently to mark the
beginning of the experiment with the support of the central
authorities.
</P>
<P>
Tendering documents were sent to 10 suppliers, five of which
were accepted, according to local officials in charge. This
transaction, though small, could be the beginning of new ways of
procurement by the local government, they noted.
</P>
<P>
After its pilot purchase in Shannan, the government procurement
system, via open tendering and bidding, is expected to be adopted
throughout Tibet. 
