<HEADLINE> UNICEF to Set up Base to Assist Timorese Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A base will be established
in the northern Australian city of Darwin to provide emergency
assistance to the refugee camps in West Timor, UNICEF said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 refugees have recently fled the militia
violence in East Timor to camps in the West Timorese capital of
Kupang.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Woodhouse, representative of the United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF), said in Darwin that the base would be
operational before the weekend.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF teams in the Kupang area had reported poor water and
sanitation conditions in the West Timorese camps, Woodhouse said.
</P>
<P>
Food will be dropped to the camps in West Timor, he said.
</P>
<P>
Blankets would also be airdropped to the thousands of refugees
who were unable to reach Kupang and were displaced in cold
mountainous areas of East Timor, he added. 
</P>
