<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Crude Palm Oil Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's crude palm
oil (CPO) output in August increased to 969,941 tons from 960,120
tons a month earlier, according to official figures released here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the month under review, palm kernel output increased by
3,120 tons month-on-month to 273,071 tons, while palm kernel oil
decreased by 1,186 tons to 127,351 tons and that of palm kernel
cake dropped by 3,383 tons to 151,927 tons, the Palm Oil
Registration and Licensing Authority (PORLA) said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Stock of CPO in August increased to 618,087 tons from 563,721
tons in July while stock of processed palm oil decreased from
598,149 tons to 480,785 tons, according to PORLA.
</P>
<P>
PORLA said palm oil export rose 18.6 percent month-on-month to
912,084 tons in August while imports of CPO increased by 135.95
percent to 45,979 tons.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is one of the largest CPO producers in the world and
the biggest palm oil exporter, accounting for about 60 percent of
the world market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
