<HEADLINE> Int'l Symposium on Industrial Restructuring in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province, which used to be China's industrial heartland, is
hosting a three-day international symposium on its industrial
transformation and restructuring in this capital city.
</P>
<P>
About 100 government and provincial officials, economists, and
entrepreneurs as well as representatives from several European
countries are attending the meeting, which began on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The symposium will discuss problems and solutions during
Liaoning's industrial transition period, and analyze the systems
of European countries to seek better trade cooperation between
Liaoning and Europe.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement to the symposium, Vice Minister of
Science and Technology Xu Guanhua said that Liaoning Province was
China's earliest heavy-industry base and has contributed a great
deal to the country and the world.
</P>
<P>
But now Liaoning must learn from the experiences of other
provinces and developed countries as it goes through industrial
transformation and restructuring, he said.
</P>
<P>
A representative from the Euro-China Cooperation and
Development Center said that European countries are concerned
about the province's industrial restructuring and are willing to
work with their Chinese counterparts to find solutions and the
proper path.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is jointly organized by China's Ministry of
Science and Technology, the Development Research Center of the
State Council, the Liaoning Provincial government, and the Euro-
China Cooperation and Development Center. 
</P>
