<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Western Pacific Polio-Free: WHO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Western Pacific region is
virtually "poliomyelitis-free" as no new cases have been reported
since March 1997, a top official of the World Health Organization
(WHO) said Wednesday in Manila.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement, Dr. Shigeru Omi, WHO Western Pacific
regional director, said credit goes to the high quality
surveillance of WHO member states, including the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"The quality of surveillance has been maintained at the highest
level throughout the region and the transmission of wild polio
virus has finally been interrupted," Omi said.
</P>
<P>
He noted, however, "this will not yet be the end of the story
of poliomyelitis eradication."
</P>
<P>
Omi said the region has to "maintain surveillance for acute
flaccid paralysis (AFP) until global certification, in order to
guard against re-introduction of imported wild polio virus."
</P>
<P>
The last polio case in the region was a 15-month-old Cambodian
girl, identified on March 19, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The WHO launched the polio eradication initiative in 1988, with
a resolve to abolish it by year 2000.
</P>
<P>
WHO's partners in the program include the United Nations
Children's Fund, the governments of Australia, Japan, South Korea,
the United States and some non-governmental organizations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China City Boosts Mobile Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Municipality in
north China set up a mobile telecom bureau as part of its ongoing
reform of the port city's telecommunications industry.
</P>
<P>
Li Yue, head of the bureau, said there are over 700,000 mobile
phones in the city, or 8.2 per hundred, three percent more than
the country's average.
</P>
<P>
The capacity of the mobile phone network in the city has
increased to 1.1 million from 1,500 in 1989, and has established
cooperative relationships with over 300 cities and areas in the
country, and some 50 companies in 33 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The mobile telecom system has now expanded its services in
diverting calls and sending and receiving short information in
English and Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the city was among the first to have introduced
competition into the telecom industry, and now both the Tianjin
Mobile Telecom Bureau and the Tianjin Branch of China Unicom are
engaged in the sector.
</P>
<P>
He added that China has in the past few months divided the
telecom and post services, and plans to separate the telecom
industry into four parts: a fixed network, mobile telecom,
wireless paging, and satellite telecom, to inspire further
development in this field.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that there were over 25 million mobile phones
in the country by the end of last year, and this figure is
expected to exceed 40 million next year, with the demand for this
year at about 15 million. The three top mobile phone dealers in
the Chinese market are Motorola, Nokia, and Ericsson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
