<HEADLINE> Asia-Europe Science Ministers to Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The first Asia-Europe Science
and Technology Minister's Meeting will be held here between on
October 14 and 15 for joint efforts to trigger overall scientific
cooperation among Asian and European countries, the Ministry of
Science and Technology announced here today.
</P>
<P>
"A wide range of subjects are expected to be discussed at the
meeting. They include cooperation principles, mechanisms, and
priority areas," said Wang Shaoqi, director of the international
cooperation department of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
He added that the meeting will also discuss a series of
subjects on the sustainable economic and social development of the
participating countries, ranging from agro-technology to basic
research.
</P>
<P>
China has taken part in two preparatory meetings in Beijing and
Brussels, respectively, where the procedures, subjects and
documents for the meeting were established.
</P>
<P>
The European Union and more than 20 countries will send
delegations led by their science ministers to the meeting, Wang
said.
</P>
<P>
At the second Asia-Europe Leader's Meeting held in London in
April 1998, Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji called on participant
countries to take concrete measures to strengthen their scientific
cooperation and hold a science minister's meeting in due time.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu said at that time that China would like to host the
gathering in 1999, and this idea was widely accepted by the Asia-
Europe countries, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Wang pointed out that the meeting will further tap Asia-Europe
cooperation potential, extend exchange channels, and set up an
effective cooperation mechanism to "create a positive impact on
Asia-Europe scientific cooperation in the 21st century."  
</P>
</TEXT>
