<HEADLINE> Illegal Sex Affairs Blamed for AIDS Spreading in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Illegal sex practices among
Zambians have been blamed for the rapid spreading of HIV/AIDS,
Zambian newspaper, The Post, reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Over 80 percent of the married men in Zambia are involved in
extra- marital sexual affairs, the paper quoted a study carried
out by the Department of Mass Communication as saying.
</P>
<P>
The study revealed most of the married men questioned in a wide
survey were maintaining more than one or more sexual partners
besides their wives.
</P>
<P>
The study was on the common practices among Zambians that had
brought about the spread of HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
It showed that polygamous marriages had also played a role in
spreading HIV/AIDS, with wives questioned saying sometimes the
epidemic was being brought into the family by the new wife.
</P>
<P>
The study noted that the inheritance of wives by the dead
husband's brother put them at risk of contracting diseases.
</P>
</TEXT>
