<HEADLINE> Eximbank Issues Financial Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- With approval from the People
's Bank of China, the China Export and Import Bank (Eximbank)
successfully issued three billion yuan (about 360 million U.S.
dollars) in two-year financial bonds through public bidding over
the past several days.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time this year Eximbank has issued policy
financial bonds through public bidding, with the latest at a
tendered interest rate of 2.91 percent.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Eximbank said the new issue carries a fixed
interest rate to be paid annually, and the principal will be
repaid when it becomes due.
</P>
<P>
He said that since its founding five years ago, Eximbank has
established an effective risk-preventing mechanism in extending
loans, and that the quality of the bank's credit assets remains
high, and the principal and interest of mature financial bonds
have all been paid, ensuring the rights and interests of creditors.
</P>
<P>
Since October 1998, Eximbank has issued financial bonds through
public bidding on four occasions, effectively cutting fund-raising
costs for the bank.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that most of the bank's loans will be
granted in the second half of this year, and that to ensure the
sufficient supply of credit capital, Eximbank will issue
additional financial bonds before the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Eximbank will launch a wider variety of
financial bonds with different terms to cater to the needs of
different investors, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
