<HEADLINE> China Continues to Ban Pyramid Schemes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A notice released recently by
the Public Security Office under China's Ministry of Public
Security asked police at all levels in China to continue the
prohibition of pyramid schemes.
</P>
<P>
All public security sections should keep a close watch on all
kinds of pyramid-type sales, including disguised forms, while
making their daily rounds, the notice said.
</P>
<P>
They should work with departments of Industry and Commerce to
fight against pyramid sales and ban them to prevent their revival.
Sever punishment should be imposed on those engaging in fraudulent
and superstitious activities, and criminal responsibility should
be defined in these cases, according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Ministry of Public Security said that
pyramid sales were abolished by the "Notice on Prohibition of
Pyramid Sales" released by the State Council last April.
</P>
<P>
"However," said the official, "these schemes in disguised forms,
such as sales promotions and sales in chain stores have recently
appeared in some areas. And they seem to be spreading."
</P>
<P>
These schemes not only cheat many people, causing them to
suffer losses, but also affect social order and stability, he
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
