<HEADLINE> Russian Helicopter Missing Over Arctic Ocean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An MI-8 helicopter with seven
people on board disappeared over the Arctic Ocean Tuesday, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter of the Russian Defense Ministry was flying from
Cape Menshikov to the village of Rogachyovo. Both localities are
in Novaya Zemlya, an archipelago in the Arctic Ocean between the
Barents and Kara seas.
</P>
<P>
Ground services lost contact with the chopper at 19:00 Moscow
time (1500 GMT) when it was 45 kilometers from Rogachyovo, Tass
said, quoting the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations.
</P>
<P>
The Emergency and Defense Ministries have dispatched two
airplanes and an MI-8MT helicopter in search of the missing
helicopter, Tass said. 
</P>
