<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Info, Technology Expo Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The 10th Asian Information
and Technology Exhibition, the largest of its kind in the region,
opened Wednesday at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center,
showcasing IT solutions for better business in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which will last through September 18, focuses
on a series of programs with an aim to remove the obstacles and
accelerate the development of information and technology in
education.
</P>
<P>
"This dovetails the local government's 'Digital 21' information
Technology strategy which is designed to enhance and strengthen
our information infrastructure and services to make Hong Kong a
leading digital city in the globally connected world," said K. H.
Lau, director of Information Technology Services, at the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 exhibitors demonstrate their advanced technologies in
six pavilions, including enterprise management, enterprise
messaging, Internet, e-commerce, information technology in
education and mobile computing.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition, a number of on-site forums and workshops
will be held to help the educational professionals to enhance
their IT knowledge and understand how to apply IT in education.
</P>
<P>
Also concurrently held with the exhibition are the Hong Kong
International Computer Conference '99, Asia-Pacific Mobile
Communication Conference 1999 and the Forum on "Linux &AMP; Open
Source - Its Now and Future".
</P>
<P>
Other features of the exhibition include Hong Kong institution
of engineers' IT village, highlights on logistic center and the
medical informatics corner.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the latest technologies, products, services and
solutions to business, this year's exhibition sees a very
substantial increase in the number of software exhibits, said
Stanley Chu, managing director of the Adsale Exhibition Services
Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"As a regional services center, there is a need and role for an
IT business solution show in Hong Kong, and we intend to further
develop our IT exhibition along this direction," Chu added.
</P>
</TEXT>
