<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Issue Souvenir Coins Commemorating 50th Anniversary of CPPCC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China,
the country's central bank, will issue ten million sets of
souvenir coins on September 16 to commemorate the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the highest advisory body of the country.
</P>
<P>
The souvenir coin, only one per set, has a face value of one
yuan, and may serve the same as the ordinary one-yuan coin.
</P>
<P>
The obverse of the coin has a picture of Zhongnanhai, the
current central leadership compound, where the first CPPCC
Conference was held on the eve of New China's founding, while the
reverse is the emblem of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
The first CPPCC Conference was held between September 21 and 30,
1949. A statement declaring the founding of the People's Republic
of China was passed at this conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan President on Judiciary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi has said that it is the wish of all Kenyans, regardless of
their status, to see justice being done in the country's courts.
</P>
<P>
Moi made the remarks Tuesday as he witnessed the swearing of
the new Chief Justice Bernard Chunga who was appointed on
September 13 by the president, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that it was through justice and fair play that
the people would have faith in the judiciary.
</P>
<P>
The president also urged the new chief justice to expedite
pending court cases, particularly those concerning corruption and
embezzlement of public funds.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the dignity of the courts must be upheld and
asked Chunga to uplift Kenya in the dispensation of justice so
that everyone would feel safe and fairly treated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
