<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22nd UPC Closes Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The 22nd Universal Postal
Congress (UPC) concluded here today after its 24-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
The congress received 599 proposals and approved 112 decisions
and resolutions, and delegates from more than 180 countries also
signed five regulations on world postal development.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jichuan, Honorary Chairman of the Congress and Minister of
the Information Industry, said at today's closing ceremony that
the congress was a great success. During the meeting, delegates
discussed reform and development of the Universal Postal Union (
UPU) and approved the Beijing Postal Strategy.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that China will continue to support the work of the UPU
and adhere to the Beijing Postal Strategy and decisions and
resolutions approved by the Congress.
</P>
<P>
The senior member of the Congress, Andre Darrigrand, said his
first impression was the high-quality reception offered by the
organizing committee when he first arrived in Beijing, and this
impression deepened during the Congress.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Leavey, secretary-general of the Congress, also highly
praised the organizing of the Congress, saying the meeting was
memorable for both its organization and the range of discussions.
</P>
<P>
Delegates also agreed to set up a technical cooperation
development fund within the UPU and hold a world postal strategy
forum between now and the next Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese organizing committee of the Congress hosted a
closing dinner for delegates this evening which included
performances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
