<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell
sharply Wednesday on fears of another interest rates rise by the U.
S. Federal Reserves in October.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index dropped 373.43 points, or 2.71 percent, to
close at 13,430.60.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover was 9.702 billion HK dollars (1.244 billion
U.S. dollars), 1.620 billion HK dollars (207 million U.S. dollars)
less than the 11.322 billion HK dollars (1.451 billion U.S.
dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Commerce Department reported on Tuesday that retail
sales rose 1.2 percent in August, resulting in the loss of 120.00
points or 1.09 percent of the Dow industrials.
</P>
<P>
The word also heightened investors' fears that the U.S. Federal
Reserve will raise interest rates in October, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
In Hong Kong, Counter of Finance, Utilities, Properties and
Commerce and Industry all suffered losses of 2.10 percent, 3.36
percent, 3.00 percent and 2.65 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 2.42 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index down 2.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong stocks opened lower Wednesday, with the Hang Seng
Index down 100.53 points at 13,703.50.
</P>
<P>
The stock prices continued to sink and closed the morning
session at 13,528.07 points, down 275.96 points or 0.21 percent.
</P>
