<HEADLINE> World Record-Holders Beaten in Chinese City Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, China, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Two women world record-
holders were beaten in the shooting competitions here on Wednesday
in the fourth Chinese City Games.
</P>
<P>
Ren Jie and Wang Xian, world record-holders in the air pistol
and the 3x20 sports rifle events respectively, were defeated in
their specialities by two teenagers.
</P>
<P>
Fei Fengji, a 17-year-old lassie from Shanghai, scored 482.9
points to beat Ren Jie by 0.1 point, becoming the sole double
champion in the shooting competition which is to be concluded on
Thursday, following her victory in the 25m sports pistol on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ren Jie only ranked second with 482.8 points, lagging far
behind her own world mark of 493.5 points last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xian from Hangzhou scored 10.6 points less than her world
mark of 689.7 points in the 3x20 sports rifle, which was
eventually won by her national teammate Zhang Shaotan in 684.7
points.
</P>
<P>
"I have played to my best, but the weather condition was not
good enough with poor visibility this morning, which was the main
reason for my failure," said Wang Xian.
</P>
<P>
In the preliminaries, Shi Jia and Li Lin, the two teenagers
from Shanghai and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, broke the 10-
year-old national junior mark by 580 and 578 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 15-year-old Zhou Jia from Guiyang, became the youngest
champion in the Games as she triumphed in the women's trap finals.
</P>
</TEXT>
