<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Export Liquefied Natural Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is expected to export
liquefied natural gas early next month as a 3.8
billion-U.S.-dollar-gas plant has begun production recently.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of Nigeria LNG Limited confirmed Wednesday that the
first consignment of the liquefied natural gas will leave its
factory in Bonny, a town in Niger Delta for Europe in October.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, one of the world's leading oil producers, is thought
to have the tenth-largest gas reserves in the world. But in the
past decades the gas emitted in Nigeria's oil fields is usually
flared off, causing enormous revenue loses and environment
problems.
</P>
<P>
The test run of the plant, virtually a city with 18,000
employees, commenced from midnight last Sunday, which was
described by the spokesman as "a landmark in Nigerian economic
history." 
</P>
</TEXT>
