<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New EU Executive Confirmed by Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The new European Commission
led by Romano Prodi was confirmed Wednesday afternoon at a
European Parliament meeting.
</P>
<P>
The new 20-member European executive team is due to take office
Thursday for its five-year term. About three-quarters of the 626-
seat assembly said they back the new Commission after president-
designate Prodi, the former Italian prime minister, promised "very,
very severe" measures against any Commissioners implicated in
criminal activity.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's voting brought to an end six months of stagnation
following the corruption scandal in which the entire Commission
had to resign on March 16, badly shaking confidence in European
institutions.
</P>
<P>
"I am determined to transform the Commission into a modern,
efficient administration which has learnt the lessons of recent
experience and put its house in order," Prodi told the members of
the parliament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the European Parliament to exercise
new powers to vote on the appointment of a new Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
