<HEADLINE> China's National Day Parade to Go Live on Web </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Internet audience across
the world can view the grand parade in celebration of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China on
the World Wide Web in real time thanks to the launch of the web
site of CHINA 10k.COM.
</P>
<P>
The parade to be held in Beijing on China's National Day (
October 1) will be broadcast live to a vast audience of academics,
well-wishers and overseas Chinese via the interactive multimedia
web site.
</P>
<P>
CHINA 10k.COM is the only web site outside China's mainland
that has been authorized by China International TV Corporation to
webcast the national day celebration.
</P>
<P>
To make the webcast possible, CHINA 10k.COM is working with
technology partners including Hong Kong-based Asia On-line Ltd.,
Microsoft Hong Kong Ltd. and Tiger Information Systems.
</P>
<P>
In advance of the webcast, CHINA 10k.COM has set an on-line "
museum" displaying a wide range of China's national treasures.
</P>
<P>
CHINA 10k.COM is the world's first multimedia interactive
Chinese history web site integrating text, voice and video.
</P>
<P>
Leveraging advanced Internet technology, the web site provides
comprehensive information on Chinese history from ancient times to
the present day. Information is available in English and in
traditional and simplified Chinese.  
</P>
</TEXT>
