<HEADLINE> Two Killed, 24 Injured in Collision in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed
and 24 others injured, six of them seriously, in a traffic
accident in South Africa early Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Two buses and a trailer were involved in the accident when the
first bus collided with a stationary trailer on the N1 highway
between Leeu-Gamka and Laingsburg in te Karoo of South Africa,
Police Inspector Rassie du Toit said.
</P>
<P>
He said the driver of the second bus tried to avoid the
accident, but it crashed into the trailer, causing the death of
the driver and a man standing next to the trailer.
</P>
<P>
Four of the seriously injured passengers have been transported
by ambulance to the N1 City Hospital in Cape Town, Toit said.
</P>
