<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Meets Argentine Attorney-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met with
Argentine Attorney-General Nicolas Eduardo Becerra and his party
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the Argentine visitors on the construction of China's
legal system in recent years, Li said that China's legislative
work has made great progress since the country introduced its
reform and opening policy 20 years ago. The supervision of the
People's Congresses at all levels in China has also been
reinforced, Li added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China's procuratorate bodies play an
important role in the country's effort to build a socialist
country ruled by law.
</P>
<P>
China and Argentina enjoy a traditional friendship and the
procuratorates of the two countries have established cooperative
ties, Li said, adding that the present China visit by Nicolas
Eduardo Becerra will further advance cooperation between the
procuratorates of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Nicolas Eduardo Becerra said that the experience of China's
procuratorate is worth learning, and that Argentina is ready to
strengthen exchange and cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Nicolas Eduardo Becerra is visiting here at the invitation of
Han Zhubin, Procurator-General of China's Supreme People's
Procuratorate  
</P>
