<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE) index fell Wednesday amid dull market where market players
preferred to sell to book profits rather than taking new positions
in the wake of the uncertain political situation.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 index closed 10.41 points, or 0.89 percent lower to
1,153.88 against Tuesday's 1,164 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume traded Wednesday stood at 77.292 million
shares against 98.219 million shares the previous day.
</P>
<P>
"Another consequent day of the bearish spell was recorded at
the market where lack of interest was prevailing throughout the
day and the investors remained unconvinced to enter the market due
to the political situation in the country," said Faisal Abbas, a
dealer with Ali Hussain Rajabali Ltd.
</P>
<P>
He said the overall market sentiment was bearish and despite
normal selling pressure, the market could not properly absorb it,
resulting in continued selling in blue chip stocks.
</P>
<P>
Of the 196 active issues, losers beat gainers 81 to 49 while 66
remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
