<HEADLINE> 10 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in a military operation
on Tuesday in eastern Turkey, an official statement said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that the Turkish security forces had exchanged fire
with a group of PKK militants near Yuksekova town of Hakkari
province bordering Iran.
</P>
<P>
During the armed clash, the security forces shot dead 10 PKK
rebels in the region, added the statement.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over
37,000 lives in conflicts between the government troops and the
PKK. 
</P>
