<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Active Fiscal Policy Viable for Next Year:Vice-Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China will surely continue to
carry out an active fiscal policy next year because expanding
domestic demand is a long-term governmental plan, Vice-Minister in
charge of the State Development Planning Commission (SDPC) Li
Rongrong said here today.
</P>
<P>
Li told a press conference held by the Press Office under the
State Council today that continuously increasing investment in
construction of basic infrastructures will add at least one
percentage point to economic growth this year.
</P>
<P>
China issued an additional 60 billion yuan of treasury bonds
this month to fund infrastructure projects and technological
development.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the investment made by the central government will
activate 200 billion yuan of investment by banks, local
governments, and enterprises in a chain reaction this year.
</P>
<P>
He said that most infrastructure projects will take three years
to complete, and so the government will continue to carry out an
active fiscal policy next year in order to guarantee the
completion of these projects.
</P>
<P>
Li said that compared to government investment in
infrastructures last year, the spending of the treasury bond money
will be focused on technological upgrading of state-owned
enterprises and the commercialization of hi-tech products.
</P>
<P>
He said that government investment in these two areas will
trigger 66.5 billion yuan of additional investment in
technological upgrading, and 21.3 billion yuan of additional
investment in localization of key industrial equipment and the
commercialization of hi-tech products.
</P>
<P>
Most of this money will be spent on purchasing new equipment
and technology, thus stimulating production in the manufacturing
and metallurgical industries.
</P>
<P>
"This year's government investment will have an even more far-
reaching impact on the economy than that of last year," he said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that such investment will take time to affect the
economy, he said the growth-promoting power of this year's fiscal
policy will be strongly felt over the next year.
</P>
<P>
Since the enterprises involved are the most healthy state-owned
enterprises and technological companies with the greatest market
potential, they will contribute greatly to economic growth by
carrying out these projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
