<HEADLINE> Net Launched to Enhance Mainland-HK Business Info Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A database network to
enhance business information exchange between Hong Kong and China'
s mainland was officially launched here Wednesday by the Hong Kong
Productivity Council (HKPC) and 30 China Productivity Centers
Association (CPA).
</P>
<P>
The China Productivity and Promotion Net (China PPNet) is
supported by over 30 provincial and municipal productivity centers
in the mainland, Thomas Tang, executive director of HKPC, said at
a ceremony to launch the net.
</P>
<P>
"Through the China PPNet, local companies will be able to
obtain the latest trade and business information from the mainland
to help them develop new products to meet the changing market
needs. At the same time, mainland users could acquire Hong Kong
and overseas' business information for product development," Tang
said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, Kwong Ki-chi, secretary for
information technology and broadcasting of Hong Kong, said that
the system will help to improve the productivity of enterprises in
both Hong Kong and the mainland, and encourage a wider adoption of
information technology, thereby enhancing their competitiveness
and building a sound foundation for the future development of
electronic linkage between the two places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
