<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Timeshare Conference Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Pacific Timeshare
Conference hosted by U.S. Resort Condominium International (RCI)
opened here today, with more than 200 representatives from around
the world attending the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Timesharing is the practice of taking a resort accommodation
unit such as an apartment, hotel room or condominium and dividing
its use rights into weekly segments. The use rights are then sold
to a consumer for a finite period of time such as 20, 30, or 40 or
more years through a membership marketing program.
</P>
<P>
Timesharing is one of the fastest-growing segments of the
travel and tourism industry, enjoyed by 4.5 million people
worldwide and with an annual turnover of approximately 6.5 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
David Clifton, group managing director of RCI Asia-Pacific Pte
Ltd., said that China is a country rich in history, tradition, and
culture, and its beautiful scenery, delicious food and friendly
people add to its charms.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his confidence that more foreign tourists will
come to China for sightseeing and vacations as a result of the
constantly improving tourist services.
</P>
<P>
There are currently 14 RCI-affiliated resorts in China's key
gateway cities, such as Beijing and Shanghai, with more in the
pipeline. RCI has also sent many people to China through timeshare
exchanges, boosting the number of tourist arrivals.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that from January to July this year, China
has received more than 40 million overseas tourists, a jump of 15.
13 percent over the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
