<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Partially Cancels Ethiopian Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Russia has, in principle,
agreed to cancel 80 percent of the 35 billion rubles (about 5.8
million U.S. dollars) it lent to Ethiopia for arms purchasing when
Mengistu Haile-Mariam was in power.
</P>
<P>
The 67 percent of the remaining 20 percent may also be reduced
through the Paris club, the Reporter newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources was quoted as saying that the debt relief was
stalled because Russia wanted Ethiopia to pay its debt on the
currency exchange rate when the money was given while Ethiopia
intended to pay its debt with the current exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
Mengistu, who took Ethiopian power in February 1977, was
overthrown in May 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
