<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Senior Citizens Set Cycling Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- About 1,500 elderly people in
the capital of China's Sichuan Province spent three hours cycling
around the city today for a record ride that was confirmed by the
Shanghai Office of the Guinness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
The average age of the participants, who included a retired
general, retired teachers, officials, and workers, and farmers,
was 65. The oldest was 82. They are members of a bicycling club
that was set up ten years ago. The route followed today was about
30 kilometers long.
</P>
<P>
The club has had many cycling activities for the elderly that
involve visits to almost every part of the country. The total
distance they've covered is 5,000 kilometers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
