<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Interest rate fears returned
to the fore in the Australian stock market Wednesday, driving
prices down across the board.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index shed 37.8 points to finish
at 2,938.1, just above its low for the day of 2,933.1.
</P>
<P>
Industrial stocks lead the fall with the all industrial index
dropping 63.8 points to close at 5,046.1.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index also lost ground, finishing 18.2 points
lower at 1,303.5.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks were particularly affected by the interest rate
jitters, with the index slumping 95.9 points to 6,106.4.
</P>
<P>
Sector leader National Australia Bank sank 50.6 cents to 22.75
Australian dollars, Commonwealth lost 39.3 cents to 23.307
Australian dollars, Westpac slipped 15.9 cents to 9.35 Australian
dollars and ANZ dipped seven cents to 10.20 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
