<HEADLINE> CPC Inter-Party Contacts See Remarkable Progress in 50 Years (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Inter-party contacts between
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and political parties worldwide
witnessed remarkable progress during the past five decades since
the founding of new China in 1949, and China's ruling party is
making active efforts to build a favorable environment for the
country's national interests.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the CPC has contacts with 340 political parties,
including both ruling and opposition parties, in 140 countries.
Exchanges are more frequent between the CPC and major political
parties in China's neighbors. Even in countries which have not
established diplomatic ties with China, the CPC has made reliable
friends in political circles, preparing for the eventual
normalization of state-to-state relations.
</P>
<P>
Ideologial differences are no longer barriers to forming
friendly cooperation between the CPC and other parties.
</P>
<P>
All these changes mark the evolution of the CPC's external
contacts during the past five decades.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
