<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Inter-Party Contacts See Remarkable Progress in 50 Years (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the eve of the birth of the People's Republic, an iron-
curtain fell between the socialist and capitalist countries, and
it was the socialist countries who first recognized New China.
Communist parties and progressive forces followed suit, breaking
the embargo and sanctions of the West by extending their friendly
hands to the newborn state.
</P>
<P>
In 1956 the CPC held its Eighth National Congress, and
representatives from 56 foreign Communist parties were present at
the CPC's invitation, creating an unprecedented situation for CPC'
s external contacts.
</P>
<P>
In the ensuing years, the CPC sustained the heated theoretical
debate inside the international Communist movement, during which
the CPC stood firm against chauvinism in an effort to safeguard
the independence and self-reliance of both China and the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The Party itself also went down the winding path in the decade-
long "cultural revolution," during which the CPC's external
contacts retrogressed.
</P>
<P>
China in the late 1970s initiated the reform and opening-up
drive by shifting its focus to economic construction. China's
diplomatic work also concentrated efforts on seeking a favorable
international environment for massive construction. In line with
such a historic change, the CPC's external contacts department
also changed its guidelines away from choosing friends merely on
the basis of ideology, thus injecting impetus to CPC's external
work.
</P>
<P>
This change marked the beginning of a new era.
</P>
<P>
The CPC's external contacts in the following years expanded
from Communist parties to national or democratic parties, and from
socialist parties to right-wing conservative parties.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Inter-Party Contacts See Remarkable Progress in 50 Years (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the early 1990s, the former Soviet Union and eastern Europe
bloc dissolved, and the African continent saw wave after wave of
multi-party transformation. All these earthshaking events brought
profound changes to the structure of political parties all over
the world.
</P>
<P>
The CPC in this period maintained its adherence to the four
principles guiding inter-party exchanges, namely, independence,
complete equality, mutual respect, and non-interference in each
other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to its open-mindedness, the CPC's attitude won
recognition and the appreciation of political parties worldwide,
creating another peak of its external contacts.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC, announced at the
15th CPC National Congress in 1997 that the CPC was willing to
develop new types of inter-party relations of exchange and
cooperation with all the political parties of various countries
which are ready to have contacts with the CPC with a view to
promoting relations between countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990915.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Inter-Party Contacts See Remarkable Progress in 50 Years (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, told Xinhua that the CPC at the turn of the
century summarizes its historic experience and has set forth the
future direction for its external work on the basis of adhering to
Deng Xiaoping's ideas on inter-party relations.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the CPC has been and will be focused on
serving the development strategy of the State and the Party in its
external work. The work, which is an integral part of overall
Chinese diplomacy, is aimed at creating a more favorable
international peace environment for the reform and opening-up and
modernization construction, he pointed out, adding that external
exchanges after the 15th CPC National Congress were enriched
thanks to such guidelines.
</P>
<P>
To improve the Party building and the development of the State,
the CPC added new content, including the exchange of experience in
party and state management, into its contacts with foreign parties,
injecting more substantial content into the exchanges.
</P>
<P>
As a new millennium approaches, it is believed that the CPC
will score more achievements thanks to the solid foundation laid
over the past 50 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
