<HEADLINE> Inmates Riot at Malaysia's Drug Rehabilitation Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian police
arrested 64 inmates at a drug rehabilitation center in the
northern state of Perak Wednesday after some 200 inmates of the
center rioted Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The inmates at Perlop II Drug Rehabilitation Center at Sungai
Siput rioted after two policemen tried to arrest four inmates
found loitering outside of the center, Bernama news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
"Police are still looking for three inmates who fled the
center," Perak police assistant superintendent Abu Bakar Mustaffa
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Police recovered from the center an assortment of weapons,
including knives, iron pipes, sticks and chains, the police
officer said.
</P>
<P>
He said the incident was the most serious among five cases of
rioting reported at the center in the past four years although
there was no damage to the center's property and no one was
injured.
</P>
<P>
All officers, staff and their family members at the center were
moved from their quarters near the center Wednesday morning to a
nearby workshop to avoid any untoward incidents, the police
officer said.
</P>
<P>
He said the 64 inmates, being held at two police stations,
would be produced in court by Thursday for remand orders to be
issued against them. 
</P>
