<HEADLINE> Urgent: Strong Earthquake Jolts Bolivia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 6 on the
Richter scale shook a remote region of Boliva early Wednesday, but
no damage or injury were reported immediately, a report reaching
here from Bolivian capital city of La Paz said.
</P>
<P>
Bolivian Observatory of San Calixto said the quake's epicenter
was about 800 kilometers southeast of La Paz.
</P>
<P>
The first report came from Tarija, with some 1,000 residents,
said people felt the tremor, but no damages or victims.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bolivian Geophysical Institute said the quake was at
least 200 kilometers below the surface.
</P>
<P>
Experts said quakes of magnitude 6 are capable of causing
severe damage, but officials doubt it had much impact considering
the depth of the earthquake. 
</P>
