<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC Extends Reconstruction Aid to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) on Wednesday informed Turkey that it has allocated
400 million U.S. dollars in reconstruction aid to the country
following last month's killer earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The message was enclosed in a letter to Turkish Foreign
Minister Ismail Cem from GCC Secretary General Jamil Al-Hujailan,
the Kuwait News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Turkish ambassador to Saudi Arabia, who received the letter,
expressed appreciation for the GCC generosity, which he said would
reflect positively on bilateral relations between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The aid was approved at the GCC foreign ministers' meeting in
the Saudi Red Sea port city of Jeddah last Saturday. The GCC
groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the United
Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
A devastating tremor, which measured at 7.4 on the Richter
scale, ripped through northwest Turkey on August 17, killing more
than 15,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
