<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Application to Fill Vacancy of Macao SAR Lawmaker Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The half-month long application
for a vacancy in the legislature of the future Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) ended Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11 Macao residents asked for application forms at
the Macao Office of the Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee
for the Macao SAR from September 1 to 15. Four of them managed to
glean the required 20 or more supporting signatures from the
members of a 199-member Selection Committee.
</P>
<P>
Relevant application data of the four people will be examined
by the chairman and vice-chairmen of the Preparatory Committee and
the name list of formal candidates will be announced later,
according to Tina Ting Yee Ho, deputy secretary-general of the
secretariat.
</P>
<P>
On September 19, the candidates will meet the Selection
Committee members, and an election will be held the following day,
Tina said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with relevant regulations, elected members of the
current Legislative Assembly of Macao, which is now under
Portuguese rule, can apply to become lawmakers of the first
Legislative Council of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
In mid-August, 15 out of the 16 elected current legislators
requested continued membership. And their qualification were
approved at the 10th plenary session of the Preparatory Committee
held at the end of August.
</P>
<P>
However, the seven legislators appointed by the Macao governor
are not able to pass through the handover on December 20.
</P>
<P>
The current Macao Legislative Assembly has 23 members. The
future Legislative Council shall have the same number, including
16 elected members and seven appointed by the chief executive of
the Macao SAR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
