<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at GMT1440, September 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- An MI-8 helicopter with seven people on board
disappeared over the Arctic Ocean Tuesday, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter of the Russian Defense Ministry was flying from
Cape Menshikov to the village of Rogachyovo. Both localities are
in Novaya Zemlya, an archipelago in the Arctic Ocean between the
Barents and Kara seas.
</P>
<P>
Ground services lost contact with the chopper at 19:00 Moscow
time (1500 GMT) when it was 45 kilometers from Rogachyovo, Tass
said, quoting the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations. (
Russia-Chopper-Missing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia's National Defense Forces (TNI) said
Wednesday it can accept Australia leading the multinational force
to East Timor if it is the decision of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
"If God is willing, TNI and all the Indonesian people will
accept the (U.N.) decision because Indonesia should put themselves
as part of the international community," TNI spokesman Maj. Gen.
Sudrajat said here.
</P>
<P>
In New York, the U.N. Security Council Wednesday morning
unanimously adopted a resolution authorizing the establishment of
a multinational force to restore peace and security in East Timor.
(Indonesia-E.Timor-Peacekeeping Force)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- At least eight persons were killed and more than a
dozen injured in Taliban's air raids on opposition-held Taloqan
city in northern Afghanistan, opposition sources said.
</P>
<P>
They said Taliban jets struck the city, capital of Takhar
province, in retaliation of the recent success of opposition
troops in capturing a number of mountain posts in Khanabad
district of Takhar province from the Islamic militia. (
Afghanistan-Taliban-Bombing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The new European Commission led by Romano Prodi was
confirmed Wednesday afternoon at a European Parliament meeting.
</P>
<P>
The new 20-member European executive team is due to take office
Thursday for its five-year term. About three-quarters of the 626-
seat assembly said they back the new Commission after president-
designate Prodi, the former Italian prime minister, promised "very,
very severe" measures against any Commissioners implicated in
criminal activity.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's voting brought to an end six months of stagnation
following the corruption scandal in which the entire Commission
had to resign on March 16, badly shaking confidence in European
institutions. (EU-Executive)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- An earthquake measuring 6 on the Richter scale shook a
remote region of Boliva early Wednesday, but no damage or injury
were reported immediately, a report reaching here from Bolivian
capital city of La Paz said.
</P>
<P>
Bolivian Observatory of San Calixto said the quake's epicenter
was about 800 kilometers southeast of La Paz.
</P>
<P>
The first report came from Tarija, with some 1,000 residents,
said people felt the tremor, but no damages or victims. (Bolivia-
Earthquake)  
