<HEADLINE> Naked Student "Surfs" Tar on S. African Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A Welsh student brought
traffic on the busy N1 highway outside Cape Town to a halt Monday
when he fell naked from a minibus, South African Press Association
(SAPA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to SAPA, the student has been making good progress in
hospital after undergoing surgery on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old student, who does not want to be identified,
and a group of fellow students visited the Stellenbosch wine
route. On their way back, they were in a "rather jolly mood", an
eyewitness was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
It appeared as if the students were playing some kind of game
in which they had to get rid off their clothes. The Welsh student
joined in the fun and in the spirit of things, decided to give
passing motorists a "moonie" (puts his pants down and show his
backside).
</P>
<P>
He pressed his bare backside against the emergency window, but
apparently pushed too hard and landed up in the middle lane of the
N1 highway.
</P>
<P>
Motorists had to swerve and brake to avoid the naked student
who was " surfing" behind the minibus on his naked backside, SAPA
said.
</P>
<P>
He lost a lot of skin on his buttocks and back. The road had to
be closed for the emergency helicopter to land, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Two fellow students, in the final year of their medicine
course, had to get dressed first before they could give
professional attention to their wounded friend.  
</P>
</TEXT>
