The members of the group are all members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference. They visited places where Mao Zedong and Zhou Enlai
lived and worked in Chongqing during the years of revolution and
the Chongqing Chang'an Automobile Co., Ltd., a state-owned
enterprise, where they made suggestions on reforms in the state-
owned sector.
</P>
<P>
They said they are deeply concerned about local education and
hope that the local government will allocate more to education. On
the environmental protection issue, some of them said that it is
necessary to curb soil erosion on the upper reaches of the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
The visit was part of the countdown activities until Macao's
return to the motherland in about three months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
