<HEADLINE> Cyprus Shocked by Death of Greek Alternate FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Leaders in Cyprus Wednesday
expressed "shock and sadness" for the unexpected death of Greece's
Alternate Foreign Minister Yiannos Kranidiotis and paid tribute to
his contribution to Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The Cyrus-born 52-year-old minister and five other people,
including his 23-year-old son, were killed when their aircraft
plunged from a high altitude before landing at the Bucharest
airport in Romania.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides said Kranidiotis' unexpected
death was "a national tragedy" at a crucial time for Cyprus and
has left "a void because he knew the Cyprus issue very well and as
a Cypriot he had a special interest in Cyprus."
</P>
<P>
And he extended condolences to Kranidiotis' family.
</P>
<P>
While describing Kranidiotis' death as "an unexpected tragedy,"
Cyprus Parliament Speaker Spyros Kyprianou said that the late
Greek minister was always involved in solving the Cyprus issue and
in the island's cause of accession to the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Political parties here have also expressed "shock and deep
sorrow" for the death of Kranidiotis.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has declared a three-day mourning period with flags
flying at half-mast to mourn Kranidiotis' death. 
</P>
