<HEADLINE> Industrial Park for Chinese Students Returning From Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, the coastal city in
China's Liaoning Province, today began construction work on three
industrial parks for people who have studied abroad and returned
to start their own businesses or do research.
</P>
<P>
The parks, which cover an area totaling 40,000 square meters,
are located in the city's high-tech industrial park. The
construction is another move by the city government to attract
overseas students. They will be provided with favorable tax,
housing, and other policies to assist them.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech industrial park has already attracted a number of
scholars and students from the United States, Japan, Germany and
Canada who have set up 13 enterprises in electronic information,
biological engineering, and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
According to a Ministry of Education official, in 1996, the
cities of Yantai and Shanghai took the lead in establishing
special industrial parks for returning Chinese scholars. There are
now more than 30 such parks across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
