<HEADLINE> China's Railways Gearing Up For 21st Century (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When that line is completed, the trip from Beijing to Shanghai
will take just 6 hours, instead of the 12 hours it takes today.
</P>
<P>
China has 12,575 km. of electrified railway lines, accounting
for 19 percent of the combined length of all railway lines and
handling a quarter of the transport volume.
</P>
<P>
In the first decade of the next century, the length of
electrified lines is expected to increase to 16,000-18,000 km., or
27 percent of the combined length of all railway lines.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that the railways have used 5.2 billion U.S. dollars
worth of overseas funds, mainly provided by the World Bank, the
Asian Development Bank, or government loans, and there are now
some 180 Sino-overseas equity and contractual joint ventures in
the railway sector, providing key equipment for the country's
railways.
</P>
<P>
China has also exported 2.4 billion U.S. dollars worth of
locomotives to 20 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Fu concluded by saying that they will try to increase exports
of railway products, but that overseas funds and expertise are
needed to achieve this goal.  
</P>
