<HEADLINE> China's New Radio And Global Position System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A new positioning and
navigation system that uses radios and the Global Position System
(GPS) was put into use today in China.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to help coastal navigation and marine fishing,
surveys, mapping, exploration, and national defense.
</P>
<P>
It has eight stations in Yanwei in Jiangsu Province; Shitang in
Zhejiang Province; Zhenhaijiao in Fujian Province; Luyu, Sanzao,
and Naozhou Island in Guangdong Province; and Baohujiao and Sanya
in Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
It covers most of China's coastal regions and will allow ships
to navigate closer to seashore and cut navigation costs. In eight
months of trial operations, it showed its accuracy and
contribution to safer navigation. 
</P>
