<HEADLINE> FIFA to Finalise 2002 World Cup Details in Las Vegas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The 2002 World Cup finals and
related issue will be discussed during the FIFA Executive
Committee in Las Vegas on October 1 and 2, the world governing
body confirmed in Lausanne on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The executive committee will confirm the time-frame for the
World Cup and discuss the controversial possibility of the finals
beginning at the end of May and ending before the end of June,
avoiding the rainy season in host countries South Korea and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Also on the agenda for ratification by the world governing body
is the agreement reached earlier this month between FIFA President
Sepp Blatter and Asian Football Confederation President Sultan
Ahmad Shah.
</P>
<P>
The agreement resolved the differences that arose following the
walk-out of the Asian national associations at the FIFA
Extraordinary Congress in Los Angeles last July.
</P>
<P>
The executive committee will also examine the GOAL project, a
report from the Chairman of FIFA Sports Medical Committee
regarding doping controls in football, details of which will be
revealed for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Progress up-dates will be presented by the relevant committees
on the Under-17 World Championship New Zealand 1999, the Club
World Championship Brazil 2000, the Olympic Football Tournaments
Sydney 2000 and the Futsal World Championship Guatamala 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
